ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: MUSI 998 serves as a workshop for students to discuss their ideas for the prospectus/dissertation, with the goal of helping students choose an advisor and begin drafting the prospectus.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course contributed immensely to my dissertation in that it greatly helped me to focus my ideas and start writing sooner than my usual habit, which had been to wait until I had all the research completed before beginning to write. I found that I can actually synthesize ideas much more quickly by writing very soon after I read a source, rather than waiting to compile all my materials. The skill of writing quickly is one that I will need to continue to develop both in my work as a graduate student, as I continue to work on my dissertation, and in my eventual career as an academic. For me, this was the most valuable part of the course.
